But most valuable were our spiritual conversations.

00:20:36.710 --> 00:20:39.150
There's so much from that sister.

00:20:39.150 --> 00:20:42.869
Once we were talking a group of us about what

00:20:42.869 --> 00:20:45.710
our relationship to Jehovah really means.

00:20:45.710 --> 00:20:49.710
And Gertrude gave us her idea, her understanding

00:20:49.710 --> 00:20:51.470
of her relationship with Jehovah.

00:20:51.470 --> 00:20:54.589
She said, you know, sometimes in life,

00:20:54.589 --> 00:20:56.990
a situation presents itself.

00:20:56.990 --> 00:21:01.109
And it's so personal and so touching

00:21:01.109 --> 00:21:05.029
that you don't tell anybody about it, except Jehovah, of course.

00:21:05.029 --> 00:21:07.589
And she said, so you prayed at Jehovah,

00:21:07.589 --> 00:21:09.670
and you prayed at Jehovah.

00:21:09.670 --> 00:21:11.509
And then passed a little time,

00:21:11.509 --> 00:21:13.869
and you feel he's answered your prayer.

00:21:13.869 --> 00:21:16.789
She said, you know, that is like a little thread

00:21:16.789 --> 00:21:19.269
that unites you with Jehovah.

00:21:19.269 --> 00:21:22.630
Now, this is the only person in the universe

00:21:22.630 --> 00:21:25.309
that shares this experience with you.

00:21:25.309 --> 00:21:27.470
So it's very personal.

00:21:27.470 --> 00:21:31.390
OK, time goes by another situation presents itself.

00:21:31.390 --> 00:21:34.269
And you pray again, well, here's another thread.

00:21:34.269 --> 00:21:36.029
And over a period of time, you've

00:21:36.029 --> 00:21:40.630
got a bunch of threads connecting you with Jehovah.

00:21:40.630 --> 00:21:44.670
And she says, and those threads are all knitted together.

00:21:44.670 --> 00:21:48.670
And they form a cord that unites you with Jehovah.

00:21:48.670 --> 00:21:51.670
And then she'd say, and don't you ever do anything

00:21:51.670 --> 00:21:54.349
to endanger that relationship.

